datachangelog 0.0.0.9000

Evaluate and log changes in data records

changelog.Rd

A function to evaluate and log changes in data records between two dataframes and optionally create a markdown changelog.

Usage

changelog(
  x,
  y,
  by = "column",
  report = FALSE,
  file = "CHANGELOG.md",
  author = NULL,
  date = NULL,
  ver = NULL
)

Arguments

x

data.frame. A data.frame to compare against y. Treated as the original version of the data records.

y

data.frame. A data.frame to compare against x. Treated as the replacement version of the data records.

by

character. How should x and y be compared? Options include by "column" (the default) or "row".

report

logical. If TRUE, a verbose report will be written to file.

file

character. Path, name, and extension of the file to be saved. Defaults to current working directory and "CHANGELOG.md".

author

character. The author of to report in the changelog report, if requested.

date

character. The data to report in the changelog report, if requested. By default, the current date is used.

ver

character. The version number to report in the changelog report, if requested.

Value

A data.frame containing data record comparison results. Only changes are reported. If report is TRUE, a changelog report will also be saved to file.

Details

This function assumes that input data.frames maintain the same structure and aims to evaluate whether existing record values have been changed (e.g. through data cleaning).

Examples

# Dataset
x <- mtcars
# Shuffled dataset
y <- x[sample(nrow(x)), ]
# Evaluate differences
changelog(x = x, y = y)
